>Live Chat Improves Your Service</strong><br/>It s not just convenience and familiarity that drive customers to companies offering online chat; customers know the service is better. They know that, depending on the web page they come from, they ll be directed to an appropriate representative. They may not know that records of every email and previous chat will be pulled up when they initiate another chat, but they will be glad they don t have to repeat their story to yet another agent. Populate a knowledgebase with your company s answers to common customer queries and your agents can provide this information at the click of a button. Your company presents itself in a more-organized and more-informed way. Your customer is satisfied far more quickly and this saves you time   lots of time."]},"id":"d607036b-d704-40e9-ab92-6761b39c0a5b","type":"text"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["<strong>Live Chat Saves Money</strong><br/>The time you save because of improved service means that a single well-informed agent can often do the job of three phone operators. A phone call requires an operator s undivided attention until he or she has found the needed information. With live chat, the operator can often assist three or more customers at the same time. Appropriate canned responses can be offered and the operator can add needed personal comments while working with other customers. This increased efficiency saves your company money. And, when it comes to generating revenue, studies conclude that more than half of the merchandise added to online shopping carts goes unpurchased. If your agent uses live chat to reach out to these undecided buyers, sales often increase dramatically. So, you may also be interested in live chat if your company wants to employ less support staff or increase sales.","<strong>Helps Guide Growth </strong><br/>While your agents are chatting, many forms of data are being collected. Frequently visited pages are logged. Records of the most-purchased products are being generated. Pre- and post-chat surveys are gathering data about peak live chat times, the topics customers are interested in and who your best support agents are. The business benefits of this data are immeasurable. A savvy marketing department can use this information to manage inventory. Human resources can use the information to staff support in appropriate numbers at times of peak usage. Company executives can use these reports to understand who their customers are, where they are and what company changes would serve these customers best.","<strong>Beat the Competition</strong><br/>When you add together improved service, increased customer loyalty, significant financial savings and data that helps guide company growth, you have an edge that may well put you ahead of your competition. If you re interested in a service that provides benefits for companies and the customers they serve, live chat software may make the difference that can help you lead your market.","Customers today are all about saving time and money while receiving the best value and service. Live chat support software can help your company provide this type of value to your customers at the same the derived data enables better business decisions. More customers and a better-run business mean a larger market share no matter what your industry. Check out the business benefits of live chat software and see if they can help your company become bigger, stronger and more profitable."]},"id":"706c79ef-6a5b-4906-a4c8-5e79cb56a554","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"article_page_8790","url":"/top-five-business-benefits-of-a-live-chat-support-system","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"lynda-angelastro","url":"/author/lynda-angelastro","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Lynda Angelastro","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"iJqwET8ThNWCtNBejE3QeP","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2014-09-24T14:42:03Z","datePublished":"201